The proposed change is a staged refactor: MacBook becomes the sole controller and YAML-state authority; hzpc becomes a compute-only node; SIG/Spot remains an existing elastic execution adapter. The current YAML state semantics, automation-ticket boundary, strategy-truth protections, and SIG/Spot compatibility must be preserved. No credentials may enter task/result packages, and a disconnected or replaying compute node must never duplicate state transitions. The revised plan explicitly defines versioned request/result YAML envelopes, controller-only result application, adapter ownership under the existing runner node, and an old-controller-before-new-controller cutover.

Hunt specifically for: hidden coupling in the current modules, state-ownership violations, migration hazards, missing idempotency or failure handling, unsafe deployment assumptions, and unnecessary abstraction. Do not modify files or run commands. Return an explicit final verdict in this form:

